723689f-b.title: Manhattan: University Place - 13th Street
723689f-b.text:
(1)
UUniversity Place and Union Square West, north from and including
13th Street, from 107 University Place, south of 13th Street.
The old buildings on the west side, from 13th to 14th Streets,
antedate 1890. The small ones in the southern half of the
block must be a good deal older than that.
On the horizon may be seen the Metropolitan and New York Life
Insurance Buildings on Madison Square.
February 24, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from 13th Street, not showing the N.W. corner and
adjoining houses.
At 14th Street University Place becomes Union Square West,
merging with Broadway. 1-3 Union Square West, shown on the N.W.
corner of 14th Street, is tho old Lincoln Building, antedating
1891, and probably named after the statue of Lincoln which stands
in front of it on Union Square. At 3l Union Sduare, on the N.W.
corner of 16th Street, aay be seen the 19-story Bank of the
Metropolis, built around 1906, and now a branch of the Bank of
Manhattan.
February 24, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO RLPRODOCTIONS.
